Cook bacon in large skillet over medium heat until crisp. Remove bacon and reserve 1 tablespoon of drippings. Meanwhile, peel, core and slice apples into rings. Add butter to same skillet, reduce heat to medium-low. Stir in reserved bacon drippings and apples. Cook, stirring occasionally, 10 minutes or until apples are crisp tender. Stir in brown sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg. Cook, stirring gently, 5 to 8 minutes longer, or until apples are tender and a syrupy glaze has formed.